This paper deals with the containment problem for Conjunctive Regular Path Queries (CRPQs), which are a type of navigational query language used in ontology and graph database querying. This topic is highly relevant to the field of database systems (cs.DB) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI), as well as to the area of logic in computer science (cs.LO). The paper also involves complexity analysis, which is a common theme in the subfields of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
